    "13318285": {
      "title": "Epithelial-mesenchymal transition and the stem cell phenotype",
      "abstract": "Epithelial-mesenchymal transition (EMT) is a developmental process in which epithelial cells acquire the motile, migratory properties of mesenchymal cells. In a recent issue of Cell, Mani et al. (2008) show that induction of EMT stimulates cultured breast cells to adopt characteristics of stem cells."
